{0 Document outline}

Expose the current Markdown file as a hierarchical symbol tree for editor
outline panels and breadcrumbs. This feature implements
[textDocument/documentSymbol] only; vault-wide [workspace/symbol] search is
out of scope.

{1 Symbols}

The outline is built from the file entry in {!Oystermark.Vault.Index}:

{ul
  {- Headings are symbols named by their displayed text. They nest according
     to heading level, including skipped levels.}
  {- Caret block IDs are key symbols named [^id].}
  {- Explicit attribute anchors are key symbols named [#id].}
}

An anchor belongs to the deepest heading that precedes it. Anchors before the
first heading are top-level symbols. Symbols without source locations are
omitted.

{1 Ranges}

A heading's selection range is its heading node. Its full range covers the
section through the byte before the next heading of the same or a higher
level, or through the end of the document. Anchor range and selection range
both cover the indexed anchor node.

Positions are converted according to {!page-"feature-utf16-positions"}.

{1 Result}

The server advertises [documentSymbolProvider] and returns hierarchical
[DocumentSymbol] values in source order. An unindexed or non-Markdown file
returns no symbols.

